# Python Style & Quality

- Write readable, explicit code; prefer meaningful names; annotate public APIs.
- Enforce ruff/flake8; type-check with mypy; maintain test coverage (see `.coveragerc`).
- Keep functions focused; avoid deep nesting; handle edge cases early.
- Do not add import-time side effects; optional deps must be guarded/imported locally.

Quality tools also include xenon, deptry, and importlinter where configured.
